          <h2 style="font-size:22px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:30px !important">Brics Summit Starts Today</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The upcoming BRICS summit in Kazan, Russia, will bring together <a href="https://www.euronews.com/2024/10/21/putin-to-host-brics-summit-in-a-bid-to-advance-russias-own-interests" target="_blank">world leaders</a> like Vladimir Putin, Xi Jinping, Narendra Modi, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, and Masoud Pezeshkian. Despite Western isolation attempts due to the Ukraine war, the summit highlights Russia‚Äôs defiance and <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-66525474" target="_blank">BRICS</a>‚Äô growing influence as the bloc expands to include countries like Iran and Saudi Arabia.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Putin sees this as a crucial moment to bolster Russia‚Äôs global alliances and negotiate economic deals. China and India are key players in expanding trade and military ties, while Russia aims to bypass Western sanctions. Brazilian President Luiz Lula da Silva has <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c89l45zeq2eo" target="_blank">canceled his trip</a> to Russia for the BRICS summit due to a head injury sustained at home, requiring him to avoid long-haul flights temporarily. He will now participate in the summit via video link.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
